---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About" active="/about">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">ABOUT THE LEAGUE</span>
      <h1>How NFYLL works</h1>
      <p class="lede">Eight independent youth clubs across northeast Florida. One Saturday-morning venue. One spring season a year. Boys, grades PK through 8.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">
    <section class="how-it-works">
      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <h3>Clubs run their own programs</h3>
        <p>Each member club handles its own players — practices, coaches, equipment, registration. Some clubs have a dozen players, some have over a hundred.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <h3>NFYLL coordinates the league</h3>
        <p>Volunteer board members from across the clubs run scheduling, division alignment, and field operations. Two directors today (Dave Vernon + Sean Packer).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <h3>One field, one morning a week</h3>
        <p>All games are at Julington Creek Plantation Park, Saturday mornings, February through May. Roughly eight game days plus a season-ending jamboree.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Divisions &amp; formats</h2>
      <p class="lede">Game formats scale with age. Younger kids play small-sided; older kids play full-field 10v10.</p>
      <div class="divisions-table">
        <div class="div-row div-row--head">
          <span>Division</span><span>Format</span><span>What it means</span>
        </div>
        <div class="div-row">
          <span><strong>1st / 2nd grade</strong></span>
          <span class="format format-4v4">4v4</span>
          <span>Small-sided, no goalies, no body or stick checks. The point is touches on the ball.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="div-row">
          <span><strong>3rd / 4th grade</strong></span>
          <span class="format format-7v7">7v7</span>
          <span>Half-field play, goalies, light contact. Bridge between learning the sport and full-field rules.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="div-row">
          <span><strong>5th / 6th grade</strong></span>
          <span class="format format-10v10">10v10</span>
          <span>Full-sided rules with full equipment. Closest to high-school lacrosse, scaled to the age group.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="div-row">
          <span><strong>7th / 8th grade</strong></span>
          <span class="format format-10v10">10v10</span>
          <span>Full-sided. This is where rec-league players bridge into middle-school and travel programs.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note">NFYLL is <strong>boys only</strong>. Girls in our area play in NEFGYLL (Northeast Florida Girls Youth Lacrosse League), a separate league.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>USA Lacrosse membership</h2>
      <p>Every player and coach must be a current USA Lacrosse member — it's both league rule and source of secondary insurance coverage during play. Memberships are inexpensive and renew annually:</p>
      <ul class="usal-tiers">
        <li><strong>$15/yr</strong> — 6U (Pre-K / K)</li>
        <li><strong>$35/yr</strong> — ages 7 to 22 (basically all rec-age players)</li>
        <li><strong>$60/yr</strong> — adults (coaches and officials; bundles Level 1 cert)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Sign up or renew at <a href="https://www.usalacrosse.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">usalacrosse.com ↗</a>. Many member clubs handle this at registration on your behalf.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Board</h2>
      <div class="board-grid">
        <div class="board-card">
          <h3>David Vernon</h3>
          <p class="board-role">Director</p>
          <p>Owns site / league operations / scheduling coordination. Fleming Island Lacrosse Club.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="board-card">
          <h3>Sean Packer</h3>
          <p class="board-role">Director</p>
          <p>Owns LeagueOps tool / matchmaking / divisional balance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:board@nfyll.org">board@nfyll.org</a> for any league inquiry. Please direct registration / your-team-specific questions to your member club first.</p>
    </section>

    <aside class="legal-card">
      <h3>Nonprofit</h3>
      <p>North Florida Lacrosse Inc. (DBA <strong>North Florida Youth Lacrosse League</strong>) is a 501(c)(3) public charity, effective October 15, 2018. Donations are tax-deductible.</p>
      <p class="legal-meta">EIN <strong>83-2612765</strong> · Florida DR-14 sales-tax exemption on file.</p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--sky-wash);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .lede { color: var(--ink); font-size: 1rem; max-width: 720px; }

  .how-it-works {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 3rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .how-it-works { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .how-arrow { display: none; }
  }
  .how-step {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
  }
  .step-num {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    width: 28px; height: 28px;
    background: var(--sunshine);
    color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }
  .how-step h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .how-step p { margin: 0; color: var(--ink); font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .how-arrow { align-self: center; color: var(--sunshine); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 300; }

  .divisions-table {
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--white);
  }
  .div-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 90px 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .div-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .div-row--head {
    background: var(--sky-wash);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .format {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.22rem 0.55rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .format-4v4 { background: var(--sand-gold-soft); color: #8a5a00; }
  .format-7v7 { background: var(--sunshine-soft); color: #b04a13; }
  .format-10v10 { background: rgba(27, 77, 126, 0.10); color: var(--river-blue); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .div-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.4rem; }
    .div-row--head { display: none; }
  }
  .note {
    background: var(--sand-gold-soft);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--sand-gold);
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .usal-tiers {
    list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1rem 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .usal-tiers li {
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .usal-tiers li strong { color: var(--river-blue); font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .usal-tiers { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .board-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 1rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .board-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .board-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
  }
  .board-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .board-role {
    color: var(--sunshine);
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .board-card p:last-child { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--ink); }

  .legal-card {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--river-blue);
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
  }
  .legal-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--river-blue); }
  .legal-card p { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .legal-card p:last-child { margin: 0; }
  .legal-meta { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem !important; }
</style>
